    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>Commonly used as novelties,<em>holo grenades</em> can create all sorts of illusions in a harmless but surprising and often amusing way. A holo version of the @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.equipment.Op1pND4wEWA3YQ7E]{Wonder Grenade} (creating only an appearance of the listed effects) is popular among fey and children. However,<em>holo grenades</em> have less innocent uses as well—criminals and infiltrators use<em>holo grenades</em> as distractions.</p>\n<p>A<em>holo grenade</em> creates a preprogrammed illusion no larger than the blast radius. The illusion functions as if you had cast<em>holographic image</em> with a level, caster level, and duration according to the grenade’s type.</p>\n<p>1st-level @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.spells.kDFNOMx78KU1GGol]{Holographic Image}; caster level 3rd; duration 2 rounds</p>"
